- Why?

683
00:34:01,376 --> 00:34:03,528
David. Is that your mother?

684
00:34:04,012 --> 00:34:06,582
Yes. That's mother.
- Did she die in this room?

685
00:34:08,199 --> 00:34:09,300
Yes, Hallie. She did.

686
00:34:11,244 --> 00:34:12,910
I hate the thought of a death around me.

687
00:34:13,686 --> 00:34:14,674
It's detestable.

688
00:34:15,131 --> 00:34:16,893
But we all know mother is happy.

689
00:34:17,564 --> 00:34:19,535
What do you mean, 'happy'? In a grave?

690
00:34:26,652 --> 00:34:29,135
You know, I don't like pictures
that look right at you.

691
00:34:30,124 --> 00:34:32,292
No matter where in the room,
they always look at you.

692
00:34:32,572 --> 00:34:33,330
See that?

693
00:34:33,527 --> 00:34:35,436
But Hallie. Mother would
love you just as I do.

694
00:34:35,722 --> 00:34:37,085
I'm not so sure she would.

695
00:34:39,342 --> 00:34:40,401
Here. Let me do it.

696
00:34:42,771 --> 00:34:45,584
Hallie, what's the matter? You seem
to have changed somehow suddenly.

697
00:34:46,675 --> 00:34:47,769
Changed? How?

698
00:34:48,174 --> 00:34:49,790
I've been watching you.
- Watching me?

699
00:34:50,262 --> 00:34:53,187
I love you, I always want to be
near you, watching your moods.

700
00:34:55,537 --> 00:34:57,125
How have I changed? How?

701
00:34:58,294 --> 00:35:00,211
You have always been so confident and ..

702
00:35:00,687 --> 00:35:01,964
You seem to doubt yourself.

703
00:35:02,628 --> 00:35:04,708
Why should I doubt myself? Doubt what?

704
00:35:05,655 --> 00:35:08,225
You said mother wouldn't have loved
you when you know she would have.

705
00:35:10,637 --> 00:35:12,576
Has anything happened
to make you unhappy?

706
00:35:17,749 --> 00:35:19,564
Hallie, is anything wrong?

707
00:35:20,494 --> 00:35:21,471
No, no.

708
00:35:25,049 --> 00:35:26,364
I'd give my life for you.

709
00:35:27,342 --> 00:35:28,491
I think you would.

710
00:35:28,847 --> 00:35:31,059
Hallie, I love you. I love you so much.

711
00:35:31,468 --> 00:35:32,592
Yes, I know you do.

712
00:35:36,524 --> 00:35:37,797
Hallie darling, look at me.

713
00:35:39,220 --> 00:35:41,236
There is something in your
eyes, something way back.

714
00:35:41,433 --> 00:35:43,020
Something that seems to be crying out.

715
00:35:43,465 --> 00:35:44,137
It is.

716
00:35:44,796 --> 00:35:47,013
Hallie, don't ever be
unhappy. Don't. Please.

717
00:35:47,309 --> 00:35:48,567
I couldn't bear it.

718
00:35:54,448 --> 00:35:55,824
Come on. Run along.

719
00:35:56,348 --> 00:35:57,392
I want to be alone.

720
00:36:04,420 --> 00:36:05,492
When you're in love.

721
00:36:05,869 --> 00:36:07,702
You make such a fool
of yourself, don't you.

722
