735
00:36:52,493 --> 00:36:53,977
In our home.
- Yes, I know.

736
00:36:55,332 --> 00:36:56,803
What are you going to do, father?

737
00:36:57,836 --> 00:36:58,708
I don't know.

738
00:36:59,635 --> 00:37:01,100
You should have stayed with him.

739
00:37:01,321 --> 00:37:03,131
I warned him.
What more could I have done?

740
00:37:03,408 --> 00:37:04,843
You should have stayed with him.

741
00:37:05,446 --> 00:37:06,630
Poor little David.

742
00:37:07,154 --> 00:37:08,691
Poor little fool.
- Mark.

743
00:37:09,035 --> 00:37:10,531
Ask this salesman Carr about her.

744
00:37:10,807 --> 00:37:12,808
She married David for money.
- Nevertheless ..

745
00:37:13,488 --> 00:37:16,140
They're married.
She bears the name of Stone.

746
00:37:16,337 --> 00:37:17,409
You can buy her off.

747
00:37:18,103 --> 00:37:20,422
How about David if he loves her?
How about him?

748
00:37:21,140 --> 00:37:21,784
Well.

749
00:37:22,256 --> 00:37:24,350
He'll get over it.
It's for his own good.

750
00:37:24,947 --> 00:37:27,139
There must have been some
reason for David loving her.

751
00:37:27,336 --> 00:37:28,122
No reason.

752
00:37:28,414 --> 00:37:31,807
A fine boy like that must have
seen some good in the girl.

753
00:37:32,888 --> 00:37:34,079
Good?
- Now, Mark.

754
00:37:34,661 --> 00:37:36,231
Who of us is without sin?

755
00:37:36,736 --> 00:37:38,202
We must be kind.

756
00:37:38,594 --> 00:37:41,077
Whatever she's been,
she's entitled to her chance.

757
00:37:41,601 --> 00:37:43,662
If thine eye offend thee, pluck it out.

758
00:37:44,377 --> 00:37:46,057
It is your eye that's offended, Mark.

