00:37:46,799 --> 00:37:49,307
I haven't seen the girl.
- Wait until you do and you see her.

760
00:37:49,504 --> 00:37:51,679
Her trade is written on her face.
- Now Mark, stop that.

761
00:37:59,910 --> 00:38:00,811
Are you ready?

762
00:38:04,193 --> 00:38:05,852
Isn't that sunset wonderful?

763
00:38:07,099 --> 00:38:08,731
All this peace after the city.

764
00:38:09,181 --> 00:38:10,211
I like cities.

765
00:38:11,036 --> 00:38:13,369
The bigger and the noisier
they are, the better I like them.

766
00:38:16,559 --> 00:38:18,428
This place is so quiet it depresses me.

767
00:38:22,183 --> 00:38:24,509
But you'll get used to it.
You'll find yourself.

768
00:38:25,052 --> 00:38:26,354
No I won't. I don't like it.

769
00:38:27,600 --> 00:38:29,745
You get old and crabby
in places like this.

770
00:38:30,480 --> 00:38:31,374
It gets you.

771
00:38:31,970 --> 00:38:34,456
Look how it got that brother of yours.
That .. Mark.

772
00:38:35,257 --> 00:38:36,015
That one.

773
00:38:36,512 --> 00:38:37,677
Just the sudden change.

774
00:38:37,874 --> 00:38:40,581
I haven't changed. Why do you
keep on saying I've changed?

775
00:38:40,903 --> 00:38:42,394
I'm never going to change. Never.

776
00:38:43,283 --> 00:38:44,024
Come on.

777
00:38:47,646 --> 00:38:49,018
You'll never change to me.

778
00:38:50,699 --> 00:38:51,924
And I'll never change.

779
00:39:00,867 --> 00:39:02,025
Do you see what I mean?

780
00:39:02,288 --> 00:39:04,664
We have all the patents on
all this new equipment.

781
00:39:04,886 --> 00:39:06,459
I showed Mr Stone in the city.

782
00:39:07,425 --> 00:39:08,356
Hello there.

783
00:39:08,788 --> 00:39:09,801
Well, well.

784
00:39:13,210 --> 00:39:15,133
The bride herself. How are you, kid?

785
00:39:15,330 --> 00:39:16,642
What you doing here?

786
00:39:16,964 --> 00:39:19,167
Mr Stone asked me up.
- Hallie.

787
00:39:19,662 --> 00:39:21,873
Hallie, meet Mr Hammond.
This is our foreman.

788
00:39:22,225 --> 00:39:23,974
This is Mrs Stone, Jack.
- How do you do?

789
00:39:24,309 --> 00:39:26,498
Glad to meet you, Mrs Stone.
Congratulations.

790
00:39:26,849 --> 00:39:27,521
Ha-ha.

791
00:39:27,967 --> 00:39:29,483
Thank you. Ha-ha.

792
00:39:33,764 --> 00:39:35,587
Have you seen the
view from here, Hallie?

793
00:39:36,877 --> 00:39:39,180
Thank you Mr Carr for your patience.
Put him up for the night.

794
00:39:44,442 --> 00:39:45,794
Father. How are you?

795
00:39:47,456 --> 00:39:48,179
Hallie.

796
00:39:51,994 --> 00:39:52,637
Well?

797
00:39:53,233 --> 00:39:54,532
Here we are, Mr Stone.

798
00:39:55,411 --> 00:39:57,011
Here is the happy pair.
- Yes.

799
00:39:58,204 --> 00:40:00,350
Weren't you surprised?
- Yes, I was.

800
00:40:01,083 --> 00:40:03,156
But Dad, I sent you a
telegram right after.

801
00:40:03,522 --> 00:40:04,650
Yes, David. You did.

802
00:40:05,180 --> 00:40:08,386
You don't look at all like the irate
parent they have in story books.

803
00:40:08,583 --> 00:40:10,368
When the hero runs off with the heroine.

804
00:40:10,608 --> 00:40:12,531
No, father is not that sort at all.

805
00:40:12,948 --> 00:40:13,975
I know you're not.

806
00:40:16,290 --> 00:40:17,711
Mark. Come on.

807
00:40:22,163 --> 00:40:23,035
Come on, you.

808
00:40:23,327 --> 00:40:24,850
Come on and join the family party.

809
00:40:27,135 --> 00:40:28,230
Oh Hamlet.

810
00:40:28,981 --> 00:40:31,399
I am thy father's ghost.

811
00:40:31,661 --> 00:40:33,733
Suppose you come and
talk to me for a while?

812
00:40:34,004 --> 00:40:35,077
Would you like that?

813
00:40:35,274 --> 00:40:36,697
Sure .. I'd love it.

814
00:40:37,068 --> 00:40:38,227
Then I come too.
- No.

815
00:40:38,569 --> 00:40:41,250
No. You stay here and listen
to some of this man's jokes.

816
00:40:42,240 --> 00:40:43,618
He's a very funny man.

817
00:40:44,504 --> 00:40:45,534
Very funny.

818
00:40:52,576 --> 00:40:53,743
Hmm .. nice.

819
00:40:54,356 --> 00:40:55,600
You like books, don't you.

820
00:40:56,921 --> 00:40:58,906
Yes, very much.
- David told me.

821
00:40:59,582 --> 00:41:01,699
What is this?
- Wheat and corn.

822
00:41:02,150 --> 00:41:03,989
And that?
- Those are the beans.

823
00:41:04,326 --> 00:41:05,169
I like corn.

824
00:41:06,037 --> 00:41:07,739
You can eat this stuff, can't you?
- Yes.

825
00:41:09,512 --> 00:41:11,071
Terrible.
- Tell me.

826
00:41:11,637 --> 00:41:13,447
What part of the country are you from?

827
00:41:13,790 --> 00:41:14,433
Iowa.

828
00:41:14,654 --> 00:41:16,205
Iowa? Well, well.

829
00:41:18,093 --> 00:41:19,182
Do you love David?

830
00:41:21,067 --> 00:41:22,907
Mr Stone. Speaking of love.

831
00:41:23,516 --> 00:41:25,148
My son Mark says you do not.

832
00:41:25,951 --> 00:41:27,710
That Mark. He'd say anything.

833
00:41:28,342 --> 00:41:29,795
Say, how did he get that way?

834
00:41:30,189 --> 00:41:31,913
But you're not answering my question.

835
00:41:32,964 --> 00:41:34,881
Do you really love David?

836
00:41:35,385 --> 00:41:37,144
If I didn't, why should
I have married him?

837
00:41:37,964 --> 00:41:39,437
Still, you're evading my question.

838
00:41:39,662 --> 00:41:40,539
Evading what?

839
00:41:41,405 --> 00:41:44,407
Could you go on living here
now you are David's wife?

840
00:41:44,928 --> 00:41:46,015
Living our lives?

841
00:41:47,138 --> 00:41:50,109
Now, Mr Stone. I don't know yet
what kind of a life that would be.

842
00:41:50,487 --> 00:41:52,004
And yet you married him?

843
00:41:52,432 --> 00:41:54,017
You agreed to share his life.

844
00:41:54,237 --> 00:41:55,939
What are you driving at, Mr Stone?

845
00:41:56,482 --> 00:41:57,338
Just this.

846
00:41:58,592 --> 00:42:00,774
We are men who believe in the <i>one</i> woman.

847
00:42:01,772 --> 00:42:03,027
The <i>one</i> love.

848
00:42:04,088 --> 00:42:05,818
David has been nurtured in that thought.

849
00:42:06,554 --> 00:42:08,017
Ever since he was a child.

850
00:42:08,747 --> 00:42:11,116
We are simple people.
- I get you. Sure.

851
00:42:11,674 --> 00:42:14,581
Say, if this thing didn't work out,
I could always be on my way.

852
00:42:15,339 --> 00:42:17,385
I'd always planned another
kind of a life anyway.

853
00:42:17,582 --> 00:42:19,602
Why didn't you follow
the life you'd planned?

854
00:42:20,063 --> 00:42:20,707
Well.

855
00:42:20,984 --> 00:42:23,677
Because David came along
and he loved me and ..

856
00:42:24,393 --> 00:42:26,643
There you are.
- But you didn't love him.

857
00:42:27,128 --> 00:42:28,312
You don't love him now.

858
00:42:29,347 --> 00:42:31,504
That boy gave you his life.

859
00:42:32,349 --> 00:42:34,608
This thing will crush him.
- No, sir. He'll get over it.

860
00:42:34,891 --> 00:42:35,792
Get over what?

861
00:42:36,629 --> 00:42:38,434
Well, if it doesn't work out.

862
00:42:43,169 --> 00:42:44,145
I love that boy.

863
00:42:45,767 --> 00:42:46,804
He is my flesh.

864
00:42:48,088 --> 00:42:49,459
I've watched him grow.

865
00:42:49,985 --> 00:42:51,885
From the time when I
could hold all of him.

866
00:42:52,505 --> 00:42:53,720
In my one hand.

867
00:42:54,363 --> 00:42:55,149
Until now.

868
00:42:57,051 --> 00:42:58,220
In his eyes.

869
00:42:58,873 --> 00:43:01,893
I can see the reflection
of the woman I loved.

870
00:43:04,936 --> 00:43:05,554
My.

871
00:43:06,306 --> 00:43:07,598
<i>One</i> woman.

872
00:43:09,077 --> 00:43:10,041
She's gone.

873
00:43:11,746 --> 00:43:14,572
But even though it was God who took her.

874
00:43:16,777 --> 00:43:18,299
The agony of her going ..

875
00:43:19,627 --> 00:43:21,313
Is .. here.

876
00:43:23,483 --> 00:43:24,203
Here.

877
00:43:28,101 --> 00:43:29,626
You mustn't hurt.

878
00:43:30,830 --> 00:43:31,714
That boy.

879
00:43:32,455 --> 00:43:35,104
I don't want to hurt him.
- Then why did you come here?

880
00:43:35,581 --> 00:43:38,362
Why did you marry him?
- Don't you talk to me like that.

881
00:43:38,942 --> 00:43:40,401
Mark talked to me that way too.

882
00:43:40,641 --> 00:43:42,891
Mark was right about you.
- Now you stop it.

883
00:43:43,468 --> 00:43:44,973
I'm going.
- Yes, go.

884
00:43:46,299 --> 00:43:47,021
Hey.

885
00:43:47,738 --> 00:43:49,440
Who do you all think
you all are, anyway?

886
00:43:49,908 --> 00:43:50,494
Go.

887
00:43:52,540 --> 00:43:54,416
I'm going .. but remember.

888
00:43:55,674 --> 00:43:59,150
I'm Mrs David Stone and I've
got something coming to me.

889
00:43:59,788 --> 00:44:00,546
How much?

890
00:44:01,365 --> 00:44:02,008
What?

891
00:44:02,912 --> 00:44:04,013
How much do you want?

892
00:44:04,210 --> 00:44:04,882
To go?

893
00:44:05,377 --> 00:44:07,724
Yes .. and never see him again.

894
00:44:10,236 --> 00:44:10,893
Well.

895
00:44:11,975 --> 00:44:12,925
You give me.

896
00:44:13,327 --> 00:44:15,730
Fifty thousand dollars and I'll
never see him again. Never.

897
00:44:17,703 --> 00:44:19,412
Never see him again?
- No, no.

898
00:44:26,458 --> 00:44:27,699
Fifty thousand dollars.

899
00:44:28,456 --> 00:44:30,117
And he'll find some nice girl, I'm sure.

900
00:44:30,615 --> 00:44:31,744
It will be just right.

901
00:44:33,294 --> 00:44:34,054
David.

902
00:44:34,392 --> 00:44:35,521
Don't go in that room.

903
00:44:35,883 --> 00:44:37,079
What's he saying to her?

904
00:44:37,791 --> 00:44:39,860
What should he be saying
to a creature like that?

905
00:44:40,910 --> 00:44:41,784
Creature?

906
00:44:43,732 --> 00:44:44,490
Creature?

907
00:44:45,497 --> 00:44:46,181
Mark.

908
00:44:50,956 --> 00:44:52,113
Take that back.

909
00:44:55,375 --> 00:44:56,386
Take that back.

910
00:44:59,220 --> 00:45:01,315
And your other cheek, you hypocrite.

911
00:45:02,709 --> 00:45:03,444
Down.

912
00:45:50,238 --> 00:45:51,010
Hammond.

913
00:45:51,619 --> 00:45:53,631
Hammond .. come quick.

914
00:46:06,325 --> 00:46:07,864
Mark.
- He hit me.

915
00:46:10,275 --> 00:46:10,891
Go.

916
00:46:12,257 --> 00:46:13,088
Get out.

917
00:46:13,793 --> 00:46:14,957
Get out!
- I'm going.

918
00:46:25,771 --> 00:46:26,589
David.

919
00:46:28,109 --> 00:46:29,784
David.
- Yes, Mr Stone.

920
00:46:55,418 --> 00:46:56,578
Come on, lightning.

921
00:46:57,122 --> 00:46:58,938
Where have you been?
What have you got there?

922
00:46:59,818 --> 00:47:01,571
Hallie Hobart. 417.

923
00:47:01,768 --> 00:47:03,184
I know. Where's the rest of it?

924
00:47:03,484 --> 00:47:05,653
Up in the room.
She hasn't finished packing yet.

925
00:47:06,022 --> 00:47:07,584
No? She goes out tonight.

926
00:47:07,936 --> 00:47:09,638
We must get this stuff
down to the depot.

927
00:47:09,835 --> 00:47:10,473
Hey.

928
00:47:11,917 --> 00:47:13,333
They're having a party up there.

929
00:47:16,156 --> 00:47:17,744
Listen Charlie, before we go in there.

930
00:47:18,207 --> 00:47:19,885
Make it snappy. I got a thirst.

931
00:47:20,204 --> 00:47:22,250
You'll see a change in her.
It isn't the same Hallie.

932
00:47:22,537 --> 00:47:24,327
Women are always changing, Monk.

933
00:47:25,001 --> 00:47:26,263
See if I got this right.

934
00:47:26,917 --> 00:47:29,388
Brother Mark took a swing
at the white-haired boy ..

935
00:47:29,585 --> 00:47:31,430
And the kid had to have an operation.

936
00:47:31,910 --> 00:47:35,304
Hallie grabbed herself a new
bankroll and is back in the big city.

937
00:47:35,501 --> 00:47:38,190
She's buying everything in sight.
She has two suites knocked into one.

938
00:47:38,634 --> 00:47:40,146
Tomorrow she shoves off for Paris.

939
00:47:40,343 --> 00:47:41,559
That's the story?
- Yes.

940
00:47:41,756 --> 00:47:44,571
Lucky girl. I'd say it was a
break in the right direction.

941
00:47:48,088 --> 00:47:50,487
Listen Charlie, it isn't a
break in the right direction.

942
00:47:51,409 --> 00:47:53,461
She's brooding Charlie.
Brooding all the time.

943
00:47:53,672 --> 00:47:55,508
Monk, you're still stuck on her.
- Of course.

944
00:47:55,794 --> 00:47:56,784
I always will be.

945
00:47:56,981 --> 00:47:58,695
Love agrees with you, kid.
You look fine.

946
00:47:59,154 --> 00:48:00,913
I've been on the wagon
since Dad's funeral.

947
00:48:01,305 --> 00:48:03,795
I'm in the firm now, Charlie.
I'm all set to marry her.

948
00:48:04,266 --> 00:48:05,539
You're in the firm?
- Yep.

949
00:48:05,788 --> 00:48:08,647
Hallie isn't going to turn
you down, kid. Not Hallie.

950
00:48:09,055 --> 00:48:09,928
Here you are.

951
00:48:11,481 --> 00:48:12,364
Thanks.

952
00:48:16,113 --> 00:48:16,842
Charlie.

953
00:48:17,118 --> 00:48:18,920
I can't get her alone.
She's never alone.

954
00:48:19,319 --> 00:48:21,723
She has a gang around her all the time.
- Who's she got?

955
00:48:22,705 --> 00:48:25,452
Fellows in the orchestra and
girls who hang around the hotel.

956
00:48:26,013 --> 00:48:27,000
Stuck on anybody?

957
00:48:27,492 --> 00:48:29,974
There's a new tenor that sings
downstairs with the orchestra.

958
00:48:31,122 --> 00:48:31,885
A tenor?

959
00:48:32,185 --> 00:48:34,440
She's stuck on anyone that will
stay up with her. And drink.

960
00:48:35,320 --> 00:48:36,881
Did you say 'drink'?
- Yes.

961
00:48:37,172 --> 00:48:38,386
I thought you did.

962
00:48:38,933 --> 00:48:40,444
Let's go.
- Charlie, listen.

963
00:48:41,189 --> 00:48:42,347
She's leaving tomorrow.

964
00:48:42,627 --> 00:48:44,562
It means a final break
with the family if I ..

965
00:48:44,894 --> 00:48:46,252
Pull up stakes and follow her.

966
00:48:46,686 --> 00:48:47,882
And I .. well ..

967
00:48:48,464 --> 00:48:49,937
I couldn't go on here without her.

968
00:48:50,479 --> 00:48:51,895
What do you want me to do, Monk?

969
00:48:52,241 --> 00:48:54,468
She likes you, Charlie.
You're sort-of a buddy. You know.

970
00:48:55,284 --> 00:48:57,072
She'll tell you everything.
I know she will.

971
00:48:57,317 --> 00:48:59,319
Now .. well .. simply ..

972
00:48:59,752 --> 00:49:01,627
Try to find out what's
the trouble, you see.

973
00:49:01,963 --> 00:49:05,409
And it it's money she wants, well I've
got all the money in the world now.

974
00:49:05,796 --> 00:49:07,304
I'll see what I can do.
- Fine.

975
00:49:07,501 --> 00:49:08,716
Is that the tenor fellow?

976
00:49:08,913 --> 00:49:10,713
Yes. He's giving a
farewell party for her.

977
00:49:14,490 --> 00:49:15,481
Hello, Charlie.

978
00:49:27,006 --> 00:49:29,133
Charlie, bless your heart.
- The Queen. How are you?

979
00:49:29,330 --> 00:49:30,917
You're just in time.
- Time for what?

980
00:49:31,246 --> 00:49:32,575
I leave tomorrow.
- I know.

981
00:49:32,983 --> 00:49:34,702
You know everybody don't you?
- Sure.

982
00:49:35,003 --> 00:49:37,195
Charlie .. let's go inside.
I want to talk to you.

983
00:49:42,779 --> 00:49:43,566
That maid.

984
00:49:44,300 --> 00:49:45,944
I was better off when I didn't have her.

985
00:49:47,049 --> 00:49:48,525
Well, you got your ambition.

986
00:49:48,961 --> 00:49:50,656
Off to Paris with a bankroll.

987
00:49:50,958 --> 00:49:53,154
Yeah, a bankroll.
- Tell Papa.

988
00:49:53,828 --> 00:49:55,329
Don't let's talk about me, Charlie.

989
00:49:55,575 --> 00:49:56,986
Have a drink.
- Drinking?

990
00:49:57,309 --> 00:49:59,013
Sure, why not?
- Why not?

991
00:49:59,421 --> 00:50:01,166
Hallie, Mr Stone is calling.

992
00:50:02,525 --> 00:50:03,824
Who?
- Mr Stone.

993
00:50:04,072 --> 00:50:04,973
Stone?
- Hmm.

994
00:50:05,394 --> 00:50:07,316
Where, on the wire?
- No. He's downstairs.

995
00:50:08,438 --> 00:50:10,988
I've gone away. I'm not here.
- Alright, kid. Don't worry. Alright.

996
00:50:15,226 --> 00:50:16,227
This is dead.

997
00:50:18,303 --> 00:50:18,946
Dead?

998
00:50:19,402 --> 00:50:20,217
Who's dead?

999
00:50:20,611 --> 00:50:22,112
Who?
- What's the matter with you?

1000
00:50:22,470 --> 00:50:24,102
What did you just say just now?

1001
00:50:24,593 --> 00:50:26,084
The champagne is dead.

1002
00:50:33,712 --> 00:50:34,727
Say, what hit you?

1003
00:50:36,654 --> 00:50:37,477
Hit me?

1004
00:50:38,206 --> 00:50:38,935
Charlie.

1005
00:50:39,616 --> 00:50:42,694
Nothing has hit me but a chunk
of money and a lot of fun.

1006
00:50:43,398 --> 00:50:44,723
That's all. Look.

1007
00:50:45,032 --> 00:50:46,646
Am I starting out right?
- Sure.

1008
00:50:46,843 --> 00:50:48,416
Look at that frilled lace.
- Yeah.

1009
00:50:48,780 --> 00:50:50,944
I'm going to get a lot
of new clothes in Paris.

1010
00:50:51,671 --> 00:50:53,573
I sail on the 14th.
- Yeah, I know.

1011
00:50:53,770 --> 00:50:54,499
Come in.

1012
00:50:55,136 --> 00:50:57,782
Look at that. Isn't that pretty or not?

1013
00:50:58,714 --> 00:51:01,134
All embroidered with
crystals and .. pearls.

1014
00:51:11,258 --> 00:51:13,254
What do you want?
- I want to speak to you.

